An act for the more frequent preaching of the Gospel, and better maintenance of the ministers in the City of Bristol. England and Wales.
p. 769-772 [i.e. 4] p.
printed by Edward Husband and John Field, printers to the Parliament of England, [London : 1650]
With an order to print dated 1 April 1650. Caption title; ornament above caption; initial letter; some text in black letter. Imprint from colophon. Signatures: 6Z² . Also issued as part of a through-paged set with a table for the entire set added. Last word of first line of text: "eigh-"; first word of line below initial: "Contribution"; last word of last full line on page: "autho-". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
